      "comment": "HOW HIGH (1) showed good early speed and led throughout to score by a space when a 6 length winner at Bendigo over 425m (23.61). Solid formlines coming through his last run. Great chance again. SCOTT SIGMA (4) produced a moderate run last time when fifth at The Meadows over 525m behind Tribeca (30.50) in a Free For All. Yet to miss the placings in five runs from this box, including three wins. One of the better hopes. RIPPED PAIGE (5) has a strong record here with six wins and a minor from 10 starts. Comes off a (24.23) win last time, scoring by one length in a Grade 5 over 425m at Bendigo. Looks a key chance on best figures. HARTLAND WILLOW (7) generally performs well here at this distance.",
